prohibitory-signs.title: No tractors or motor vehicles slower than 40 km/h
Total weight limit
prohibitory-signs.desc: Restriction is for motor vehicles with more than two wheels and an allowed total weight limit above the given weight limit.

prohibitory-signs.title: Width limit
prohibitory-signs.desc: Restriction is for a vehicle including all of its goods.

prohibitory-signs.title: Height limit
prohibitory-signs.desc: Restriction is for a vehicle including all of its goods.

prohibitory-signs.title: Length limit
prohibitory-signs.desc: Restriction is for a vehicle including all of its goods.

prohibitory-signs.title: Weight limit for vehicles
prohibitory-signs.desc: Restriction is for each vehicle in the case of a lorry.

prohibitory-signs.title: Weight limit for lorries
prohibitory-signs.desc: Restriction is for the combined weight in the case of a lorry, though no single vehicle is permitted above the limit either.

prohibitory-signs.title: Axle weight limit
prohibitory-signs.desc: No vehicle with weight above the given limit for each axle, and maximum 150% of the limit for each bogie.

prohibitory-signs.title: Stop for control
prohibitory-signs.desc: Vehicle is not permitted to continue until the action described is done.

prohibitory-signs.title: Stop for tax
prohibitory-signs.desc: Vehicle is not permitted to continue until the action described is done.

prohibitory-signs.title: Stop for customs
prohibitory-signs.desc: Vehicle is not permitted to continue until the action described is done.

prohibitory-signs.title: No right turn
prohibitory-signs.desc: For the next intersection unless otherwise stated with a supplementary sign.

prohibitory-signs.title: No left turn
prohibitory-signs.desc: For the next intersection unless otherwise stated with a supplementary sign.

prohibitory-signs.title: No U-turn
prohibitory-signs.desc: Until and including the next crossroads.

prohibitory-signs.title: No overtaking
prohibitory-signs.desc: Restriction is for overtaking motor vehicles with more than two wheels. Overtaking on the right side is permitted by normal traffic rules.

prohibitory-signs.title: No overtaking for lorries
prohibitory-signs.desc: Restriction is for lorries with a total weight above 3.500 kg overtaking motor vehicles with more than two wheels. Overtaking on the right side is permitted by normal traffic rules.

prohibitory-signs.title: End of no overtaking for lorries
Speed limit
prohibitory-signs.desc: Speed limit of given km/h until new speed limit, end of special speed limit, speed limit zone or any pedestrian precinct sign

prohibitory-signs.title: End of special speed limit
prohibitory-signs.desc: This means a general speed limit of 50 km/h in populated areas and 80 km/h in rural areas by law.

prohibitory-signs.title: Speed limit zone
prohibitory-signs.desc: Speed limit of given km/h until end of speed limit, end of speed limit zone or any pedestrian precinct sign

prohibitory-signs.title: No stopping
prohibitory-signs.desc: No stops until the next crossing road or until another sign ends it.

prohibitory-signs.title: No parking
prohibitory-signs.desc: No parking on the side of the road where the sign is until the next crossing road or until another sign ends it.

prohibitory-signs.title: Parking zone
prohibitory-signs.desc: Parking permitted until end of parking zone sign. Often with supplementary text about when the sign is valid.

prohibitory-signs.title: No parking zone
prohibitory-signs.desc: No parking permitted until end of parking zone sign. Often with supplementary text about when the sign is valid.
